usage: git select [<options>] [<sku>]

Switch to a commit reference that best match the specified SKU (default to bundle branch).
Always try to attach to a dev branch first (dev affinity), then to a prod branch.

    -h|--help               display help
    -e|--stop-on-error      stop visit as soon as command fails (exit code != 0)
    -j<n>                   number of submodules selected in parallel (default to 32)
    -a|--all                visit all submodules (ignore SKU filter)
    .                       visit startup module only (do not visit submodules)

    --dev                   switch to dev branches of startup module and submodules
                              (default to dev branch of bundle and last version of submodules)
    <sku>                   SKU to be selected (default to bundle active branch)
    
example:
    git select              # switch to last published version of active SKU
    git select sku/sal/dev  # switch to last published version of specified SKU
    git select .            # switch to last published version of startup module only
    git select --dev        # switch to dev branches of active SKU
    git select --dev .      # switch to dev branch of current module only